olm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret De Plessy was born about 1207, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Mr about 1228, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1207–":"umbes 1207–Surnud","1203–Male":"1203–Surnud","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1228":"1228","1203":"1203","Abt 1207":"umbes 1207","Abt 1228":"umbes 1228","1207":"1207","Of, Heleigh, Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Heleigh Castle, Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1207–":"noin 1207–Kuollut","1203–Male":"1203–Kuollut","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1203":"1203","Abt 1207":"noin 1207","Abt 1228":"noin 1228","1207":"1207","Of, Heleigh, Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Heleigh Castle, Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1207–":"environ 1207–Décédée","1203–Male":"1203–Décédé","1228–Female":"1228–Décédée","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1228":"1228","1203":"1203","Abt 1207":"environ 1207","Abt 1228":"environ 1228","1207":"1207","Of, Heleigh, Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Heleigh Castle, Staffordshire, Englan